(2374, 1, '2015-03-31 01:34:07', '2015-03-31 01:34:07', 'Since 2010, the Council of Ontario Directors of Education (CODE) has coordinated and provided leadership for a summer literacy and numeracy learning program. Funded by the Literacy and Numeracy Secretariat, Ontario Ministry of Education, this successful program is intended to support students in the primary grades who would benefit from engaging and interactive literacy and numeracy instruction during the summer months. \r\n\r\nIn conjunction with the summer learning program, significant research studies have been carried out to examine the factors that help minimize summer learning loss and close the achievement gap. Students are invited by school staff to the summer programs, which include (in addition to literacy and numeracy instruction) a recreational component, active involvement of parents, and opportunities for Community engagement. \r\n\r\nReports have been published on the success of the summer learning program, and a program and planning guide has been developed to support boards as they implement summer programs. In addition, a number of summer learning resources have been developed by boards and are available on this website.\r\n', 'Your Summer Learning Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '66-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 01:34:07', '2015-03-31 01:34:07', '', 66, 'http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/66-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
