(2377, 1, '2015-03-31 01:37:53', '2015-03-31 01:37:53', 'Effective summer learning is closely linked to engaging and focused instruction. As someone who is responsible for coordinating, supporting and instructing the on-site literacy/numeracy program, the summer learning teacher plays a key role in developing a strategy that connects parents, students and program staff.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSummer learning teachers can grow their repertoire of literacy/numeracy strategies and resources, including developing a home reading program with parents as partners to reinforce SLP activities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn addition to the resources and planning tips available on this web site and in the SLP <a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/Summer_Literacy/SLLP%20Planning%20Guide%202014%20English_HR.pdf">Planning Guide</a>, teachers may also find helpful materials at <a href="http://eworkshop.on.ca/edu/core.cfm">eworkshop.on.ca</a>, a portal with free access to resources specifically crafted for Ontario educators seeking to improve their skills and knowledge.', 'For Teachers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2198-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 01:37:53', '2015-03-31 01:37:53', '', 2198, 'http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/2198-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
