(2406, 1, '2015-04-12 01:31:16', '2015-04-12 01:31:16', 'Since 2010, the Council of Ontario Directors of Education (CODE) has coordinated and provided leadership for a summer literacy and numeracy learning program. Funded by the Literacy and Numeracy Secretariat, Ontario Ministry of Education, this successful program is intended to support students in the primary grades who would benefit from engaging and interactive literacy and numeracy instruction during the summer months.\r\n\r\nIn conjunction with the summer learning program, significant research studies have been carried out to examine the factors that help minimize summer learning loss and close the achievement gap. Students are invited by school staff to the summer programs, which include (in addition to literacy and numeracy instruction) a recreational component, active involvement of parents, and opportunities for Community engagement.\r\n\r\nReports have been published on the success of the summer learning program, and a program and planning guide has been developed to support boards as they implement summer programs. In addition, a number of summer learning resources have been developed by boards and are available on this website.', 'Organise Your Summer Learning Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '66-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-12 01:31:16', '2015-04-12 01:31:16', '', 66, 'http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/66-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2407, 1, '2015-04-12 01:44:15', '2015-04-12 01:44:15', 'Since 2010, the summer learning program and its research protocol have had the same objective: to benefit students and reduce summer literacy and numeracy learning losses. As these reports attest, the research protocol is developing important data needed for strong evidenced-based policy making, and the further enhancement of high-quality summer programs in Ontario. And the comments, ideas, strategies and successes gathered here from the SLP community have helped summer learning in Ontario make a greater impact on more students.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Forms and Reports', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2195-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-12 01:44:15', '2015-04-12 01:44:15', '', 2195, 'http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/2195-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2408, 1, '2015-04-29 22:13:32', '2015-04-29 22:13:32', 'Since 2010, the summer learning program and its research protocol have had the same objective: to benefit students and reduce summer literacy and numeracy learning losses. As these reports attest, the research protocol is developing important data needed for strong evidenced-based policy making, and the further enhancement of high-quality summer programs in Ontario. And the comments, ideas, strategies and successes gathered here from the SLP community have helped summer learning in Ontario make a greater impact on more students.\n<h3>SLP Reports</h3>\nThe following Report has been prepared by the Literacy and Numeracy Secretariat to outline the impact of the 2014 Summer Learning Program in minimizing summer learning loss.\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Summer-Learning-Final-Report-March-23-2015.docx" target="_blank">Summer Learning Program Report 2014: Program Monitoring for Accountability</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/SummerLearning_2013_Report.pdf">SummerLearning_2013_Report</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/SLLP-report-2012.pdf">SLLP report 2012</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/SLLP-report-2011.pdf">SLLP report 2011</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Summer-Literacy-Learning_technical-appendix-2011.pdf">Summer Literacy Learning_technical appendix 2011</a>\n<h3>SLP planning guide</h3>\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/SLLP-Planning-Guide-2014-English_HR.pdf">SLLP Planning Guide 2014 English_HR</a>\n<h3>Research Reports</h3>\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Quantitative-and-Qualitative-Research-Results_2013.pdf">Quantitative and Qualitative Research Results_2013</a>\n<h3>En franais</h3>\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Le-rapport-de-2013.pdf">Le rapport de 2013</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Le-rapport-de-2012.pdf">Le rapport de 2012</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Le-rapport-de-2011.pdf">Le rapport de 2011</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annexe-technique-du-projet-dt-de-littratie-2011.pdf">Annexe technique du projet dt de littratie 2011</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/SLLP-Planning-Guide-2014-French_D2.pdf">SLLP Planning Guide 2014 French_D2</a>\n\n<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Rsultats-qualitatifs-et-quantitatifs-de-la-recherche_2013.pdf">Rsultats qualitatifs et quantitatifs de la recherche_2013</a>\n\ntude longitudinale de trois conseils scolaires de langue franaise, 2014\nL''universit d''Ottawa a complt son rapport sur les trois conseils scolaires de langue franaise participant  une tude longitudinale pour dterminer si les programmes d''t de littratie font une diffrence dans le temps. Le rapport complet est disponible seulement en franais. Chaque conseil a reu son propre rapport individuel.', 'Forms and Reports', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2195-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-04-29 22:13:32', '2015-04-29 22:13:32', '', 2195, 'http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/2195-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
