(2617, 3, '2015-06-26 14:39:07', '2015-06-26 14:39:07', 'As part of the Ministry of Educations initiatives to support 21<sup>st</sup> century learning and engage pupils in innovative and forward-thinking activities, all 72 Ontario school boards will receive robotic kits (STEM resources) in September 2015. CODE, acting on behalf of the Ministry, is organizing and managing distribution of the kits. The target group is pupils in grades 1 to 3 and 6 to 8.\r\n<p align="LEFT">Thirty-four boards will be including STEM resources/robotics in their summer learning programs on a voluntary basis this summer. By using the robotic kits in summer learning classes, students and teachers will be offered an opportunity to experiment with these resources in a small (and flexible) group setting. There is already some evidence that robotics encourage and support the development of literacy and numeracy skills, as well as problem solving, collaboration and critical thinking skills.</p>\r\n<p align="LEFT">This summer will also provide a valuable opportunity for the CODE robotic team and LNS to hear from summer learning leads and teachers about how robotics can support student learning and acquisition of literacy and numeracy skills and knowledge.</p>', 'Robotics', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2613-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-26 14:39:07', '2015-06-26 14:39:07', '', 2613, 'http://ontariosummerlearning.org/2613-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
